In the diagram, $AB$ is a line segment.  What is the value of $x$?

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(10,0),black+linewidth(1));
draw((4,0)--(4,8),black+linewidth(1));
draw((4,0)--(3.5,0)--(3.5,0.5)--(4,0.5)--cycle,black+linewidth(1));
draw((4,0)--(9,7),black+linewidth(1));
label("$A$",(0,0),W);
label("$B$",(10,0),E);
label("$x^\circ$",(4.75,2.25));
label("$52^\circ$",(5.5,0.75));
[/asy] ||| Since $AB$ is a line segment, we have that $\angle ACD + \angle DCE + \angle ECB = 90^\circ$. This gives us the equation $90^\circ + x^\circ + 52^\circ = 90^\circ$. Simplifying this gives $x^\circ = 90^\circ - 90^\circ - 52^\circ$, resulting in $x = \boxed{-52}$.

