label("$C$",C,S);
label("$D$",D,N);
[/asy]

Since $\angle ABC$ is a straight angle, we have $\angle ABD = 180^\circ - 108^\circ = 72^\circ$.  From triangle $ABD$, we have  \[26^\circ + 72^\circ + x = 180^\circ,\]  so $98^\circ + x = 180^\circ$ and $x = \boxed{82^\circ}$.

